  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Oral malodor is a common condition. In most cases this condition results from the proteolytic
      activity of anaerobic oral bacteria. These bacteria produce volatile sulfide compounds which
      are fowl smelling and are felt during exhalation and speech. the aim of the present study is
      to examine a simple method of detecting these bacteria in samples taken from the oral cavity
      of oral malodor patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
